createPluginRepoWithFirstVersion(string,.details: After the creation of the `PluginRepo` and release of the first version by the factory, ownership is transferred to the `_maintainer` address.

params._maintainer: The maintainer of the plugin repo. This address has permission to update metadata, upgrade the repo logic, and manage the repo permissions.
params._pluginSetup: The plugin factory contract associated with the plugin version.

protocolVersion().details: This version number is not to be confused with the `release` and `build` numbers found in the `Version.Tag` struct inside the `PluginRepo` contract being used to version plugin setup and associated plugin implementation contracts.

returns._0: Returns the semantic Aragon OSx protocol version number.
Returns `true` if the interface is supported.

constructor.notice: Initializes the addresses of the Aragon plugin registry and `PluginRepo` base contract to proxy to.

createPluginRepo(string,address).notice: Creates a plugin repository proxy pointing to the `pluginRepoBase` implementation and registers it in the Aragon plugin registry.

createPluginRepoWithFirstVersion(string,.notice: Creates and registers a `PluginRepo` with an ENS subdomain and publishes an initial version `1.1`.

pluginRepoBase().notice: The address of the `PluginRepo` base contract to proxy to..

protocolVersion().notice: Returns the semantic Aragon OSx protocol version number that the implementing contract is associated with.

supportsInterface(bytes4).notice: Checks if this or the parent contract supports an interface by its ID.
